product_name: Smart Seed Sun & Shade Mixture 3lb bag
review_text: I live in New England and needed some seed for an area around 18x10 in full sun. Im not an expert so I researched what the different grass seeds were in this product and seemed to fit my needs, the Perennial Ryegrass germinates fast and is good for full sun, the Tall and Fine Fescue also germinates quick and has deep roots that are more heat and drought tolerant, then the Kentucky Bluegrass is good for full sun and is good for spreading out on its own filling in bare spots and self repair.I took the time to prepare the ground, turned it over with a shovel then leveled with a rake, removed all the rocks and roots I could see. Used a hand held spreader to put the seed down, basically eyeing it until it looked like there was a good coverage. Went over it lightly with the rake so the seed was just under the top and tamped it down with the flat side of the rake. Watered daily, just enough to keep the soil damp but avoid runnoff and flooding. After 6 days I had grass growing, and it just took off from there.I have issues with wild animals and cats digging up the yard, the squirrels bury peanuts everywhere that they must be getting from a neighbor feeding them and the cats go to the bathroom, its frustrating, so I laid down a roll of chicken wire fencing I picked up and it worked at keeping everything off while allowing the grass to grow.Very happy with this grass seed, germinated quick and filled in nice. I think the prep work was important, making sure the soil was broken up and covering the seed just under the surface.
